# AI Founder TODO

Simple, clear roadmap for building a frontend-only AI tools discovery site.

## North Star

Build a fast website where users can:

- discover AI tools by goal
- filter and compare tools quickly
- trust the information
- decide with confidence

## Top Priorities

1. Structured tool data
2. Powerful search
3. Smart filters
4. Related tools
5. Comparison experience

## Current Focus (MVP)

### 1) Data Foundation

- [ ] Define `Tool` JSON schema
- [ ] Create `tool-template.json`
- [ ] Add 10 high-quality sample tools
- [ ] Enforce required fields: `id`, `slug`, `name`, `categories`, `pricing`, `platforms`
- [ ] Keep naming normalized (use one format only, e.g. `image-generation`)

### 2) Core Pages

- [ ] Homepage with global search and key sections
- [ ] Tool details page (`/tools/[slug]`)
- [ ] Category page (`/categories/[category]`)
- [ ] Compare page (`/compare`)

### 3) Search and Filtering

- [ ] Search fields: `name`, `tagline`, `shortDescription`, `categories`, `tags`, `features`, `bestFor`, `useCases`
- [ ] Add weighted ranking:
  - [ ] `name` = highest
  - [ ] `categories` = high
  - [ ] `tags` = medium
  - [ ] description text = lower
- [ ] Initial filters: Free, Has API, Beginner Friendly, Supports Arabic, Web Only, For Developers, For Students
- [ ] Create lightweight `search-index.json`

### 4) Tool Card UX

- [ ] Show logo, name, tagline, category
- [ ] Add badges: free/paid, API, beginner-friendly, Arabic support
- [ ] Add `Compare` action
- [ ] Add local bookmarks (`localStorage`)
- [ ] Track recently viewed tools

## Phase Plan

### Phase 1: MVP Build

- [ ] Folder structure
- [ ] Tool schema + template
- [ ] 10 sample tools
- [ ] Homepage
- [ ] Tool page
- [ ] Basic search
- [ ] Basic filters

### Phase 2: Product Depth

- [ ] Related tools engine
- [ ] Comparison feature
- [ ] Collections pages
- [ ] Featured tools system
- [ ] Bookmarks + history polish

### Phase 3: Intelligence Layer

- [ ] Recommendation wizard
- [ ] Better ranking model
- [ ] Search suggestions/autocomplete
- [ ] Advanced compare table
- [ ] Search performance optimization

### Phase 4: SEO + Content Scale

- [ ] SEO page templates
- [ ] Use-case hub pages
- [ ] Prompt examples per tool
- [ ] Tool update tracking
- [ ] Metadata enrichment

## Feature Checklist (Details)

### Homepage Sections

- [ ] Global search bar
- [ ] Featured tools
- [ ] Popular categories
- [ ] Free tools
- [ ] Beginner-friendly tools
- [ ] Trending tools

### Tool Details Page

- [ ] Name, logo, tagline, short and full descriptions
- [ ] Developer/company
- [ ] Categories and tags
- [ ] Main and secondary features
- [ ] Best for + use cases
- [ ] Input/output + platform support
- [ ] Pricing details
- [ ] Pros, cons, limitations
- [ ] FAQ
- [ ] Alternatives + related tools
- [ ] Privacy/trust details
- [ ] Last updated date

### SEO Pages (Later)

- [ ] `/tools/[slug]`
- [ ] `/categories/[category]`
- [ ] `/collections/[slug]`
- [ ] `/compare/[slug]`

## Technical Notes

### Data Quality Rules

- [ ] Unique `id` for every tool
- [ ] Unique `slug` for every tool
- [ ] Valid `pricing` object
- [ ] Valid `platforms` object
- [ ] No duplicate records

### Suggested Utilities

- [ ] `loadTools`
- [ ] `searchTools`
- [ ] `filterTools`
- [ ] `getRelatedTools`
- [ ] `compareTools`

## Do Not Do Early

- [ ] Avoid heavy animations
- [ ] Avoid over-complex UI
- [ ] Avoid backend before MVP proof
- [ ] Avoid building 100 features at once

## Weekly Execution Rhythm

- [ ] Monday: data updates + normalization
- [ ] Tuesday: search/filter improvements
- [ ] Wednesday: tool page quality
- [ ] Thursday: compare + related tools
- [ ] Friday: SEO/content and cleanup

## Definition of MVP Done

- [ ] At least 50 tools with clean metadata
- [ ] Search returns useful ranked results
- [ ] Filters work reliably
- [ ] Tool pages are complete and readable
- [ ] Compare works for 2-3 tools
- [ ] Site is fast and mobile-friendly
